Bank Act I
The National Banking Act imposes a system of free banking at the national level. A portion of the national banks' capital has to be government bonds. The national credit rating improves by +2 and the treasury increases by $120 million per year, but support in states fall by -3, as state banks and greenbacks will lose status. ALLOWS CONSTRUCTION OF NATIONAL BANK BUILDING.
