The Union Passes Tariff Act.
\tThe Union Government has passed an Act that allows large increases in the tariff rates imposed on foreign imports to the Union. This Act will increase the funds collected, mainly from European trading partners importing their products into Union markets.\n\tWhile Government funding is improved, at least in the short term, the European nations have been left stupefied by such an attack on their trade. Reports indicate that sympathy with the Union is decreasing in Europe.\n\tUnion corporations on the other hand, welcome the tariffs with open arms, because it helps domestic production to compete with foreign goods.
