504
Emancipation Proclamation Issued!
\tThe President of the United States has issued a proclamation and executive order, making all slaves in the secessionist Confederate States free men. As soon as a slave escapes the control of the Confederate government, either by running away across Union lines or through the advance of federal troops, the slave will be permanently free.\n\tWhile this proclamation does not include the slaves in states not in rebellion, these states are strongly encouraged to abolish slavery themselves.\n\tThe Confederate response has been open outrage. The Proclamation is seen as vindication for the rebellion and proof that Lincoln would have abolished slavery even if the states had remained in the Union.\n\tEuropeans welcome the news, as they abolished slavery earlier and the institution is seen as a barbarism and not fitting for the modern world.
