Policies in the North take full advantage of the industrial revolution at hand. With private companies investing in this expansion; new railroads are laid and profits from industry soar. The prosperity and prospect of jobs increases the number of immigrants from Europe into northern states. This steady flood of humanity increases the population of the North fast. Many of the immigrants are of catholic faith, and willing to work for lower wages than the Americans. This creates religious unrest and tensions between nationalities, reducing northern unity.
