0





0

Following the forced relocation of Native Americans from East of the Mississippi in the 1830s, known as the "Trail of Tears", Northern policies towards the natives changed, at least in principle. With further Western expansion, the agreements made with the natives are quickly forgotten and fighting continues. In these Indian Wars the U.S. military and especially junior officers gain some experience, while the settlers fulfill the "Manifest Destiny". For the natives, though, this means continuous loss of life and land, reaching the level of genocide among many tribes.
